%I A396642 #27 Jun 08 2026 16:57:52
%S A396642 60,84,120,132,140,156,168,204,220,228,240,260,264,270,276,280,308,
%T A396642 312,315,336,340,348,364,372,378,380,408,420,440,444,450,456,460,476,
%U A396642 480,492,495,516,520,525,528,532,540,552,560,564,572,580,585,594,616,620
%N A396642 Numbers k = p_1^e_1 * ... * p_i^e_i such that the area of the convex hull of the planar coordinates [p_i, e_i] is an integer >= 1.
%C A396642 At least 3 non-collinear points to form a two-dimensional shape (a polygon) with a nonzero area are needed.
%C A396642 According to Pick's Theorem, the area A of any integral polygon is determined by the formula A = I - 1 + B/2 where I is the number of integer points strictly inside the polygon and B is the number of integer points on the boundary.
%C A396642 Empirically: If A(k) is a positive integer, then A(k) < k/24. A(k) denotes the area of the convex hull (according to the described procedure) for an integer k.
%e A396642 For k = 60: k = 2^2*3^1*5^1, the area of the convex hull of the planar coordinates (2, 2), (3, 1), (5, 1) is 1 thus k = 60 is a term.
%o A396642 (Python)
%o A396642 from itertools import count, islice
%o A396642 from sympy import factorint
%o A396642 from sympy.geometry import convex_hull
%o A396642 def A396642_gen(startvalue=2): # generator of terms >= startvalue
%o A396642     for k in count(max(startvalue,2)):
%o A396642         p = convex_hull(*factorint(k).items())
%o A396642         if hasattr(p,'area') and p.area.is_integer:
%o A396642             yield int(k)
%o A396642 A396642_list = list(islice(A396642_gen(),50)) # _Chai Wah Wu_, Jun 01 2026
%Y A396642 Cf. A000040, A395113.
%K A396642 nonn,new
%O A396642 1,1
%A A396642 _Ctibor O. Zizka_, Jun 01 2026
